FBIS4-18450 "drweu065_q_94017" FBIS-WEU-94-065 Daily Report 4 Apr 1994 TURKEY PKK Radio Says Army Torched Villages PKK Radio Says Army Torched Villages NC0404195194 (Clandestine) Voice of Independent Kurdistan in Turkish 1400 GMT 4 Apr 94 NC0404195194 (Clandestine) Voice of Independent Kurdistan Turkish BFN [Excerpt] The 27 March local elections were widely boycotted in Kurdistan. Heeding the call of our party, the PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan], most of our people boycotted the elections. The number of people taking part in Kurdistan was very (?low). Even then, most of them cast invalid votes. The colonialist Turkish Republic tried to prevent our people from boycotting the elections by forcing them to go to the polling booths. The fascist Turkish Republic massacred those who resisted participation. It torched and destroyed their villages and committed savageries. These are some of the patriots killed: [passage omitted] [reception ends]
